03:04.641 --> 03:08.643
<i>Mast approaching,</i>
<i>starboard side!</i>

03:26.446 --> 03:28.329
<i>Rig the capstan!</i>

03:40.927 --> 03:42.093
<i>Sir?</i>

03:43.046 --> 03:45.046
There are men here to see...

04:06.736 --> 04:08.369
May I help you?

04:10.073 --> 04:11.405
You're Drummond.

04:13.076 --> 04:15.293
Mary's your wife.

04:15.328 --> 04:18.745
<i>Mary's our sister.</i>

04:18.748 --> 04:22.250
Caleb, Tom, and...

04:23.920 --> 04:26.754
- Edgar.
- Edgar, that's right.

04:26.756 --> 04:30.758
And you came all the way
from Williamsburg

04:30.760 --> 04:32.510
just to be upset with me?

04:32.562 --> 04:35.096
We came from Williamsburg

04:35.148 --> 04:38.349
to make sure that you
honored your vows to her.

04:38.401 --> 04:42.854
End of today, either you're gonna
be her current husband

04:42.906 --> 04:44.605
or her late one.

04:46.442 --> 04:51.112
I'm sorry, but, um, there's
someplace I have to be.

04:54.000 --> 04:55.666
You're coming with us.

04:57.036 --> 04:59.370
<i>I understand your anger,</i>

04:59.422 --> 05:00.705
<i>but I've lived long enough</i>

05:00.757 --> 05:04.125
to know that any promise made

05:04.177 --> 05:07.261
beside the word "forever"

05:07.297 --> 05:11.182
<i>is no more than a lie agreed upon.</i>

05:11.217 --> 05:13.184
<i>There is no forever.</i>

05:13.219 --> 05:17.355
Everything moves towards its end.

05:17.390 --> 05:21.309
And the closer we get to ours,
the louder that clock ticks,

05:21.311 --> 05:23.778
<i>the less a sane man</i>
<i>would let a promise</i>

05:23.813 --> 05:25.479
<i>deprive him of happiness.</i>

05:25.481 --> 05:29.233
I explained all this to Mary,

05:29.285 --> 05:30.818
who told me she understood

05:30.870 --> 05:34.405
and that she would not
protest our separation.

05:34.457 --> 05:37.625
Are you calling my sister a liar?

05:40.463 --> 05:42.246
Well...

05:42.298 --> 05:44.999
you're here.

05:45.051 --> 05:47.218
I can think of at least three lies

05:47.253 --> 05:50.137
she must have told you
to bring that about.

05:50.173 --> 05:53.507
<i>First, I imagine she told you</i>

05:53.509 --> 05:55.593
<i>I retired from a prosperous trade</i>

05:55.645 --> 05:57.678
<i>to settle with her here.</i>

05:57.730 --> 06:00.514
But what she likely did not mention

06:00.516 --> 06:03.568
is that that trade
was high seas piracy.

06:04.878 --> 06:07.745
<i>Second, she told you</i>
<i>my name was Drummond,</i>

06:07.747 --> 06:11.749
but when I plied that trade,

06:11.801 --> 06:14.635
I was called Teach.

06:15.805 --> 06:17.338
<i>And third,</i>

06:17.390 --> 06:21.142
she clearly led you to believe

06:21.177 --> 06:25.847
that you could point your sword
in my direction

06:26.599 --> 06:30.234
<i>and survive the experience.</i>

06:37.777 --> 06:42.113
This, too, was something
less than the truth.

07:11.778 --> 07:14.946
<i>Nassau awaits.</i>

07:14.981 --> 07:17.481
Let us away.

