09:11.347 --> 09:12.797
<i>Who goes there?</i>

09:14.734 --> 09:16.767
I said, "Who goes there?"

10:47.360 --> 10:50.494
You are the magistrate here.

10:50.530 --> 10:52.696
Hazzard.

10:52.749 --> 10:56.033
Bridgetown, St. Kitts,

10:56.035 --> 10:59.537
Martinique, Nevis...

10:59.539 --> 11:03.424
their magistrates
hanged men for piracy.

11:03.459 --> 11:06.710
They all receive visits from me.

11:06.712 --> 11:09.713
The word went forth...

11:09.715 --> 11:12.383
any capital sentence
served against a pirate

11:12.435 --> 11:15.719
would hear my answer.

11:15.772 --> 11:20.391
You must'a known. You must'a heard.

11:20.393 --> 11:25.196
And yet you chose to hang
those three men in your square.

11:27.950 --> 11:29.900
Why?

11:29.952 --> 11:31.902
If I didn't...

11:34.073 --> 11:39.376
if I let my fear of you
prevent me from enforcing the law,

11:39.412 --> 11:42.079
then civilization in this place is dead.

11:43.749 --> 11:48.502
I also know that most
of those other magistrates you visited,

11:48.554 --> 11:53.474
they were corrupt men, dishonest men.

11:53.509 --> 11:56.393
<i>I wagered that despite</i>
<i>all I'd heard about you,</i>

11:56.429 --> 11:58.813
<i>your mercilessness, your cruelty,</i>

11:58.848 --> 12:01.899
that you could tell the difference.

12:01.934 --> 12:03.484
That you could see
I was an honest man.

12:03.519 --> 12:05.486
<i>No!</i>

12:06.772 --> 12:09.940
No, no, no.

12:12.862 --> 12:14.495
No!

12:45.945 --> 12:48.112
<i>Keep 'em coming!</i>

12:48.114 --> 12:50.081
<i>Throw down a rope!</i>

12:50.116 --> 12:52.049
<i>We need it to pull up plunder!</i>

12:52.835 --> 12:54.752
<i>Keep movin' up</i>
<i>the decks, down below.</i>

12:59.542 --> 13:01.342
<i>How many more you got comin' up?</i>

13:01.377 --> 13:02.793
<i>Another three.</i>

13:03.379 --> 13:04.512
Is it done?

13:06.632 --> 13:07.798
It is.

13:07.850 --> 13:11.135
Once the plunder is stowed,
get us underway.

13:11.187 --> 13:12.770
Every man to his charge.

13:12.805 --> 13:14.805
Looks like we garnered
a good haul out of it.

13:14.807 --> 13:16.440
<i>Get everything into the hold.</i>

13:16.476 --> 13:18.275
The men did well
under the circumstances.

13:18.311 --> 13:19.810
Not all of them.

13:21.731 --> 13:25.483
Lost his nerve.
I want him replaced on the Vanguard

13:25.485 --> 13:27.451
before we go over the side again.

13:27.487 --> 13:29.320
He lost his footing.

13:29.322 --> 13:31.572
I don't think it had anything to do
with his nerve.

13:31.624 --> 13:33.741
Replace him.

13:37.046 --> 13:38.913
He's getting worse.

13:38.965 --> 13:40.715
He's fine.

13:40.750 --> 13:42.166
Are you sure about that?

13:42.168 --> 13:43.834
We just faced a band
of colonial regulars out there.

13:43.886 --> 13:45.169
He's entitled to a mood.

14:07.610 --> 14:09.944
Is it her?

14:09.996 --> 14:12.696
It's her.
Right where she's supposed to be.

14:17.253 --> 14:19.837
Bring us alongside.

14:19.872 --> 14:22.706
Spread your sheets!
Stand ready with grapples!

14:22.759 --> 14:24.508
<i>Spread the sheets!</i>

14:24.544 --> 14:25.793
<i>Ready the grapples!</i>

14:27.504 --> 14:29.024
<i>His men are jumping ship.</i>

14:29.048 --> 14:31.515
They aren't his men.

14:31.551 --> 14:33.768
They're his cargo.

14:33.803 --> 14:37.104
When Jack asked me to hunt her,

14:37.140 --> 14:38.939
he said she was hauling timber.

14:38.975 --> 14:41.725
He said the supplies were badly needed
for fort repairs.

14:43.062 --> 14:45.062
Funny...

14:45.114 --> 14:47.865
I don't remember him
saying anything about slaves.

